Eugene: "I wouldn't go that far -- but you have a home here if you need it. And two busted up Union men who are grateful to you. So take care, okay?"
Empathy: He really means it.
Inland Empire: He's not gonna get over it.
Jump to: [Eugenalain HUB]
You: "Could you guys help me get in to the harbour?"
Eugene: "Couldn't help you even if I wanted to." He shakes his head. "The whole harbour is in lockdown and Evrart sent word to sit tight and wait for instructions."
Eugenalain HUB
Kim Kitsuragi: "Was this really the best idea?" The lieutenant pauses to think for a moment. "I guess you may have prolonged his existence a bit. If he can still remember this when he sobers up."
Eugene: "If you think this will keep him from offin' himself, I'll make sure to remind him... so far I've just been pouring whiskey in him to keep him sedated." He nods.
Alain: His eyes, which remain fixed on yours, become somewhat clearer, and he smiles a malevolent drunken smile. "Dennis is a dead man... just doesn't know it yet..."

You: "You, Eugene."
Eugene: "Me? No, man... I'm not a leader." He smiles suddenly. "You know Titus only recruited me 'cause I play the guitar? Said the team could use the morale boost."
Eugene: "Anyone ever tell you you're a total dickhead?" His voice is quiet and resigned. "Well... you are, man. Just fuck off and leave us be."
Inland Empire: Yes. People have called you that before. You didn't care.

You: "You two are just going to go back to hauling containers in the harbour?"
Eugene: "No, man. I don't know... I guess the Union will still be policing the neighbourhood, but..." He looks at his dazed companion. "Who's gonna do it now?"
You: "I am."
Eugene: "That wouldn't be funny even if we weren't surrounded by the ghosts of our fallen friends."
Eugene: "Let's not get ahead of ourselves." He frowns. "We'll see what he does with the whole Shanky business."
Jump to: [Eugenalain HUB]
Eugene: He looks off to the side, eyes filled with worry. "I haven't *got* shit, Al."
Volition: There's something there. A germ of determination. He knows he has no choice but to rise to the occasion.
Eugene: "I will. You take care of yours," he nods to you.
Pain Threshold: A sharp pain shoots up your side and into your stomach. You must not look too good. Luckily it passes...
Eugene: "Oh, it's you... Didn't think we'd see you walking any time soon." He looks to the man behind him. "Alain, look, it's the rat cop."
Alain: "Uh... what?" He looks up, his eyes full of confusion, as if he'd just woken from a deep sleep.
Electrochemistry: He's very, *very* drunk.
Eugene: "He wasn't, that's the thing." He sighs heavily. "Titus, Theo, Dennis, Angie... they're all gone, but he got away without a scratch."
"He wasn't, that's the thing." He sighs heavily. "Titus, Theo, Dennis, Angie, Lizzie... They're all gone, but he got away without a scratch."
"He wasn't, that's the thing." He sighs heavily. "Titus, Theo, Angie, Elizabeth... They're all gone, but he got away without a scratch."
Alain: "I just..." He seems barely able to keep his head up. "...there's nothing left. NOTHING!"

Empathy: It's survivor's guilt. He feels like he should have died with the others. He may kill himself if he doesn't find a new purpose -- or else go on in this way, not dead, but not really living either.
You: "Oh yeah... that makes sense. Never mind."
Eugene: "Look, what do you want from us, man? Things are pretty tough right now."

Logic: This is not *completely* ludicrous. Him and Titus were the only detectives of the bunch. Titus more, but Eugene at least knew how to think along.
